  "title": "Senior/ Electrical Engineer",
  "description": "<ul>\n  <li>Supervise and lead the electrical team to ensure smooth project execution.</li>\n  <li>Carry out engineering work, including design, calculations, planning, and tender preparation or evaluation.</li>\n  <li>Support team growth and skill development.</li>\n  <li>Review QA/QC documents to ensure all engineering deliverables meet required standards.</li>\n  <li>Coordinate with clients, project managers, architects, and contractors to ensure effective communication.</li>\n  <li>Identify and resolve technical issues during design and construction stages.</li>\n  <li>Perform additional tasks as assigned by the project team.</li>\n  <li>Recommend improvements to enhance efficiency and project profitability.</li>\n  <li>Conduct testing and commissioning of electrical systems.</li>\n  <li>Oversee power activation and system start-up.</li>\n  <li>Ensure compliance with all electrical codes, regulations, and safety standards.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>We regret only shortlisted candidates will be contacted. All applications will be handled confidentially. By submitting your application, you agree to the collection, use, retention, and disclosure of your personal information to prospective employers.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>EA License No: 20C0270</p>\n<p>EA Personnel No: R22110980</p>\n<p>EA Personnel Name: Lim Hooi Mei</p>",
